quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  18,99,"And on that Day We will let them surge like waves over each other, and [then] the Horn will be blown, and We will gather them all together"
  18,100,On that Day We shall display Hell plainly to the unbelievers
  18,101,"those whose eyes had been veiled from My message, and who could not hear it"
  18,102,Do those who have denied the truth think that they can take My servants as protectors instead of Me? We have prepared Hell for the unbelievers as their lodging place
  18,103,"Say, \"Shall we tell you who are the most failing in whatever they do"
  18,104,"They are those whose efforts are lost in worldly pursuits, while they think that they are doing good work"
  18,105,Those are the ones who deny the signs of their Lord and deny that they will meet Him. Their actions will come to nothing and on the Day of Resurrection they will be of no consequence
  18,106,"Hell is their recompense for having denied the truth, and ridiculed My signs and My Messengers"
  18,107,Those who have believed and done righteous deeds will have Paradise for their lodging
  18,108,"where they will abide eternally, never wishing to leave"
  18,109,"Say, \"If the sea were ink for [writing] the words of my Lord, the sea would run out long before the words of my Lord ran out, even if We were to add another sea to it"
  18,110,"Say, \"I am only a man like you, to whom has been revealed that your god is one God. So, whoever looks forward with hope to meet his Lord, let him do righteous deeds and in the worship of his Lord not associate anyone with Him"
  19,1,Kaf Ha Ya 'Ayn Sad
  19,2,Recount your Lord's mercy on His servant Zechariah
  19,3,When he called to His Lord silently
  19,4,"he said, \"My Lord, my bones have weakened, and my head shimmers with grey hair, but never, Lord, have I failed to be blessed in praying to you"
  19,5,"And I fear what my kinsfolk [will do] after I am gone. My wife has been barren, so give me an heir as a gift from You"
  19,6,"one who will receive my inheritance and he will be an heir to the family of Jacob. And make him, my Lord, pleasing to You"
  19,7,"O Zechariah, We bring you good news of a son whose name will be John, a name We have never given to anyone else before"
  19,8,"[Zechariah] said, \"My Lord, how will I have a son when my wife has been barren and I have reached advanced old age"
  19,9,"He said, \"It will be so. Your Lord says: 'It is easy for Me, for I created you before, when you were nothing"
  19,10,"[Zechariah] said, \"My Lord, give me a sign.\" He said, \"Your sign is that you will not speak to people for three full nights"
  19,11,"So he came out from the sanctuary and signaled his people to glorify [God] in the morning and in the evening"
  19,12,"John, take hold of the Book with steadfastness.\" And We gave him wisdom [while he was still] a boy"
  19,13,"as well as affection from Us and purity, and he was always mindful of Us"
  19,14,"and full of kindness towards his parents, and he was not domineering or rebellious"
  19,15,"[God's] peace was upon him on the day he was born and the day of his death, and it will be upon him on the day he is raised alive"
  19,16,"Mention in the Book the story of Mary, when she withdrew from her family to a place toward the east"
  19,17,"and secluded herself from them. We then sent to her Our Spirit, who appeared to her in the shape of a perfect human being"
  19,18,"She said, \"I seek refuge from you in the Merciful, [leave me alone] if you are God fearing"
  19,19,"He said, \"I am only the Messenger of your Lord, [who says,] 'I will give you a son endowed with purity"
  19,20,"She said, \"How can I have a son when no man has touched me and I have not been a promiscuous woman"
  19,21,"He said, \"It will be so. Your Lord says, 'It is easy for Me, and We will make him a sign to people and a mercy from Us. The matter is already determined"